    "Details": "A home-grown design from the Aurigan Reach, it was designed fairly soon after the civil war situation was resolved. Built to bring a light Gauss Rifle into combat with some defensive armament around it, it mounts the rifle in the torso for stability and has an extensive set of small and medium lasers for protection against close opponents. For handling close in firepower needs, designers replaced the light Gauss Rifle with an LBX 10 while leaving the rest of the mech the same.<br><br>X-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
